# Local deploy and test

## Do not assume www.tawala.com

Legacy C# Designer **Deploy** and **Project Manager** target the live Tawala website. For AI-Tawala work, use **local** deploy only unless the owner explicitly asks otherwise.

## Deploy DirtBowl to Java (8080)

From repo root (Tomcat must be running):

```bash
node scripts/deploy-dirtbowl-java.mjs
```

- Reads `designer-web/public/samples/dirtbowl_definition_v3.json`
- POSTs XML to `http://localhost:8080/client` (credentials default `dev`/`dev`)
- May run `scripts/dev-data.sh` seed unless `TAWALA_SKIP_SEED=1`

Override: `TAWALA_JAVA_URL`, `TAWALA_DEV_USER`, `TAWALA_DEV_PASSWORD`.

## Browser Designer deploy

```bash
cd designer-web && npm run dev
```

- UI: http://localhost:5173 — **File → Deploy** or toolbar Deploy
- API: http://localhost:3001 — proxies via Vite
- For Java backend: `TAWALA_JAVA_URL=http://localhost:8080` when running API
- If Preview/Deploy fails while 5173 still loads: `./scripts/ensure-dev-api.sh` (Vite often outlives a dead API)

Credentials for local Java: prefer **`dev` / `dev`**.

## CSS / theme changes on 8080

Project CSS lives under paths like `docker/tomcat/css/project/dirtbowl2/project.css`.

After `docker cp` or file edits, **browser cache may hide changes**. Verify by opening the CSS URL directly or disabling cache in DevTools. Query string `?x=...` on deployed pages may not update when only the file on disk changes.

## Registration parity work

8080 fixes are often **export-time XML + project CSS**, not Designer-native layout. Prefer `registrationFibToXml.mjs` and theme CSS when aligning Registration pages; do not block browser Designer spec work on full visual parity unless the owner asks.
